<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Family 
<taxonomicName authority="Broch, 1916" authorityName="Broch" authorityYear="1916" family="Anthothelidae" higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="family">Anthothelidae Broch, 1916</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Branches of colonies slender. Polyps monomorphic, with prominent calyces, anthocodiae usually exsert. Axis not jointed, without a cross-chambered central core. Medulla surrounded by longitudinal boundary canals (of roughly equal size) separating it from cortex; medulla only rarely perforated by gastrodermal solenia in smaller branches and even then, not as extensively as in lower parts of colony; in larger branches, medulla perforated by solenia. Generally, medulla with separable sclerites; medullar sclerites stout spindles (not needle-like), thorny, ornamented with warts, spines or branching processes, that may link sclerites together. Sclerites of coenenchyme longer fusiform spindles, sometimes clavate or bent, occasionally with radiate bodies and capstans (rarely).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Within the Subclass 
<taxonomicName genus="Octocorallia" lsidName="Octocorallia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="subclass" subclass="Octocorallia">Octocorallia</taxonomicName>
, taxonomic placement of this family reflects the changeable history the Order 
<taxonomicName genus="Octocorallia" lsidName="Octocorallia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="order">Alcyonacea</taxonomicName>
has experienced since its inception. Currently, 
<taxonomicName genus="Octocorallia" lsidName="Octocorallia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="order">Alcyonacea</taxonomicName>
is one of three orders in the subclass (
<bibRefCitation author="Williams, GC" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" url="researcharchive.calacademy.org/research/izg/OCTOCLASS.htm" year="2001 - 2017">Williams and Cairns 2014</bibRefCitation>
). The current Order 
<taxonomicName genus="Octocorallia" lsidName="Octocorallia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="order">Alcyonacea</taxonomicName>
was, however, originally divided into four orders (
<taxonomicName genus="Octocorallia" lsidName="Octocorallia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="order">Alcyonacea</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="Octocorallia" lsidName="Octocorallia" order="Gorgonacea" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="order">Gorgonacea</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="H.Ohba, 1978" authorityName="H.Ohba" authorityYear="1978" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Stolonifera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Stolonifera" order="Saxifragales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="suborder" suborder="Stolonifera">Stolonifera</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="H.Ohba, 1978" authorityName="H.Ohba" authorityYear="1978" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Stolonifera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Stolonifera" order="Telestacea" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="order">Telestacea</taxonomicName>
). Current coral taxonomy now divides Order 
<taxonomicName authority="H.Ohba, 1978" authorityName="H.Ohba" authorityYear="1978" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Stolonifera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Stolonifera" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="order">Alcyonacea</taxonomicName>
into five nominal groups: 
<taxonomicName genus="Calcaxonia" lsidName="Calcaxonia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="suborder" suborder="Calcaxonia">Calcaxonia</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="Holaxonia" lsidName="Holaxonia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="suborder" suborder="Holaxonia">Holaxonia</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="Scleraxonia" lsidName="Scleraxonia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="suborder" suborder="Scleraxonia">Scleraxonia</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="Alcyoniina" lsidName="Alcyoniina" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="suborder" suborder="Alcyoniina">Alcyoniina</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="H.Ohba, 1978" authorityName="H.Ohba" authorityYear="1978" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Stolonifera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Stolonifera" order="Saxifragales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="suborder" suborder="Stolonifera">Stolonifera</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bayer, FM" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="902 - 947" title="Key to the genera of Octocorallia exclusive of Pennatulacea (Coelenterata: Anthozoa) with diagnoses of new taxa." url="https://repository.si.edu/handle/10088/978" volume="94" year="1981 c">Bayer 1981c</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Fabricius, KE" journalOrPublisher="Australian Institute of Marine Science, Queensland, Australia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" title="Soft Corals and Sea Fans: A Comprehensive Guide to the tropical shallow-water genera of the Central-West Pacific, the Indian Ocean and the Red Sea." year="2001">Fabricius and Alderslade 2001</bibRefCitation>
). While the Family 
<taxonomicName family="Anthothelidae" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="family">Anthothelidae</taxonomicName>
is today recognized as valid in the Order 
<taxonomicName authority="H.Ohba, 1978" authorityName="H.Ohba" authorityYear="1978" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Stolonifera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Stolonifera" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="order">Alcyonacea</taxonomicName>
[
<taxonomicName genus="Scleraxonia" lsidName="Scleraxonia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="suborder" suborder="Scleraxonia">Scleraxonia</taxonomicName>
], a number of species in the family were originally placed in the older Order 
<taxonomicName authority="H.Ohba, 1978" authorityName="H.Ohba" authorityYear="1978" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Stolonifera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Stolonifera" order="Saxifragales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="suborder" suborder="Stolonifera">Stolonifera</taxonomicName>
, often within the Family 
<taxonomicName family="Clavulariidae" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="family">Clavulariidae</taxonomicName>
. A few researchers may still group some of the families of soft corals in an Order 
<taxonomicName authority="H.Ohba, 1978" authorityName="H.Ohba" authorityYear="1978" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Stolonifera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Stolonifera" order="Saxifragales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="suborder" suborder="Stolonifera">Stolonifera</taxonomicName>
, but since then, a number of genera and several species have been moved out of 
<taxonomicName authority="H.Ohba, 1978" authorityName="H.Ohba" authorityYear="1978" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Stolonifera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Stolonifera" order="Saxifragales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="suborder" suborder="Stolonifera">Stolonifera</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Fabricius, KE" journalOrPublisher="Australian Institute of Marine Science, Queensland, Australia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" title="Soft Corals and Sea Fans: A Comprehensive Guide to the tropical shallow-water genera of the Central-West Pacific, the Indian Ocean and the Red Sea." year="2001">Fabricius and Alderslade (2001)</bibRefCitation>
noted that the &quot;decision whether to categorize a particular genus as a stoloniferan becomes so subjective that the name plainly has limited classificatory value.....&quot; Use of the Order 
<taxonomicName authority="H.Ohba, 1978" authorityName="H.Ohba" authorityYear="1978" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Stolonifera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Stolonifera" order="Saxifragales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="suborder" suborder="Stolonifera">Stolonifera</taxonomicName>
, and placement of the Family 
<taxonomicName family="Anthothelidae" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="family">Anthothelidae</taxonomicName>
in it, or the nominal group, 
<taxonomicName genus="Scleraxonia" lsidName="Scleraxonia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="suborder" suborder="Scleraxonia">Scleraxonia</taxonomicName>
(as opposed to 
<taxonomicName authority="H.Ohba, 1978" authorityName="H.Ohba" authorityYear="1978" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Stolonifera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Stolonifera" order="Saxifragales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="suborder" suborder="Stolonifera">Stolonifera</taxonomicName>
), has had a continued, tumultuous history (
<bibRefCitation author="Hickson, SJ" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Zoological Society London" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="541 - 557" title="Some Alcyonaria and a Stylaster from the west coast of North America." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1469-7998.1915.00541.x" volume="37" year="1915">Hickson 1915</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Molander, AR" journalOrPublisher="Arkiv for Zoologi" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 12" title="Der Kelch als systematischer Charakter bei den Alcyonaceen." volume="11" year="1918">Molander 1918</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Kükenthal">Kuekenthal</normalizedToken>
1919
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kuekenthal, W" journalOrPublisher="Walter de Gruyter &amp; Company, Berlin" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" title="Gorgonaria. Das Tierreich, Vol. 47." year="1924">1924</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Madsen, FJ" journalOrPublisher="Danish Ingolf-Expedition" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 65" title="Octocorallia." volume="5" year="1944">Madsen 1944</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bayer, FM" journalOrPublisher=") Studies on the Fauna of Curacao and other Caribbean Islands" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 373" title="The shallow-water Octocorallia of the West Indian Region: (A manual for marine biologists). In: Hummelinck W (Ed." volume="12" year="1961">Bayer 1961</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bayer, FM" journalOrPublisher="Academia Brasileira de Ciencia, Rio de Janeiro" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" title="Status of Knowledge of Octocorals of World Seas. Seminarios de Biologia Marinha, Sao Paulo, 9 - 15 Fevereiro de 1980." url="https://repository.si.edu/handle/10088/1237" year="1981 a">Bayer 1981a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bayer, FM" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="878 - 901" title="On some genera of stoloniferous Octocorals (Coelenterata: Anthozoa), with descriptions of new taxa." url="https://repository.si.edu/handle/10088/971" volume="94" year="1981 b">b</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bayer, FM" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="902 - 947" title="Key to the genera of Octocorallia exclusive of Pennatulacea (Coelenterata: Anthozoa) with diagnoses of new taxa." url="https://repository.si.edu/handle/10088/978" volume="94" year="1981 c">c</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hochberg, FG" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Southern California Coastal Water Research Project (SCCWRP) Taxonomic Standardization Program" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="17 - 29" title="Southern California Stoloniferans, Telestaceans, Alcyonaceans." volume="7" year="1979">Hochberg 1979</bibRefCitation>
). Currently, the classification of species in the family is determined by the presence of a membranous colony form, presence, or absence of coenenchyme layers surrounding an axis, and the way in which polyps arise from the membranous base.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Any membranous octocoral colony currently held in the SBMNH collection (few in number, small in size, deteriorated due to early formalin storage) could be a member of either the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Anthozoa" family="Clavulariidae" genus="Clavularia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Clavularia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">Clavularia</taxonomicName>
or the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Anthozoa" family="Anthothelidae" genus="Anthothela" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Anthothela" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">Anthothela</taxonomicName>
(the latter, a genus within the Order 
<taxonomicName authority="H.Ohba, 1978" authorityName="H.Ohba" authorityYear="1978" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Stolonifera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Stolonifera" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="order">Alcyonacea</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="Scleraxonia" lsidName="Scleraxonia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="suborder" suborder="Scleraxonia">Scleraxonia</taxonomicName>
). A detailed examination of the few colonies held in the SBMNH collection, in comparison with material housed elsewhere is needed; that necessitates a separate project, to be undertaken at some future date. Most of the material in the SBMNH collection with membranous colony form is present in a very fragile state; a more detailed description for each will not be easy, in some instances, not possible at all. It is likely that even with a more thorough examination of the material held at SBMNH, the results will necessarily be inconclusive. A complete revision of the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Anthozoa" family="Anthothelidae" genus="Anthothela" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Anthothela" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">Anthothela</taxonomicName>
was recently completed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Moore, KM" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination=": 1" title="A taxonomic revision of Anthothela (Octocorallia: Scleraxonia: Anthothelidae) and related genera, with the addition of new taxa, using morphological and molecular data." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4304.1.1" volume="4304" year="2017">Moore et al. (2017)</bibRefCitation>
, utilized here.
</paragraph>
